    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-23T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-23T13:00:00-05:00" n="144"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.01/18: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Higgins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-23T12:00:00-06:00"
                            >December 23, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 5:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>130. Department’s telegram No. 93, December 20, 8 p.m.<note n="8"
                        xml:id="d144fn8">See footnote 6, <ref target="#pg_183">p. 183</ref>.</note>
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs states that his Government’s policy will conform to
                    that of the United States Government with regard to the recognition of the
                    Guatemalan Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Higgins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
